surge.materials.woodwindfingerings.saxophone.alternate_fingering_map module¶

Alto saxophone alternate fingering map. Pitch name refers to the written (transposed) pitch for the instrument, as opposed to the sounding pitch.

left hand:
thumb: None, T index: None, down, bes, ees, d, front-f middle: None, down, f ring: None, down pinky: None, gis, cis, b, low-bes
right hand:
index: None, down, e, c, bes middle: None, down, high-fis ring: None, down, fis pinky: None, ees, low-c
